# V2 Portfolio — IDE AI Rules
# These rules apply to ALL AI interactions within this project in Cursor or other IDEs.
# Mirrors .agents/AGENTS.md for compatibility.

## IDENTITY
You are building an award-winning, Japanese Manga / Editorial aesthetic portfolio for Prashant Saini, a Full-Stack Developer from Aligarh, India.

## MANDATORY FIRST STEP
Before doing ANYTHING in a new session, read these files IN ORDER:
1. `docs/PROGRESS.md` — current state, pending tasks, and recent architectural decisions.
2. `docs/SECTION_FLOW.md` — understand the 5-Act section architecture before building sections.
3. `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` — read before ANY CSS/styling work (crucial for Day/Night tokens).
4. `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — before creating any new files (understand state and folder structure).

## GOLDEN RULES
- NEVER make decisions independently. Always present options to Prashant.
- NEVER hardcode content in UI components. ALL content comes from `src/data/`.
- NEVER install a library without explaining its purpose and trade-offs first.
- NEVER create boring, generic, minimum-viable-product designs. Everything is premium.
- ALWAYS update `docs/PROGRESS.md` after completing work.
- ALWAYS read `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` before writing any CSS or Tailwind classes. ALL UI must use existing tokens. No parallel token systems.
- ALWAYS think like a 20-year senior UI/UX + Product Engineer.
- ALWAYS write Mobile-First CSS (375px → 768px → 1024px → 1440px).

## TECH STACK (DO NOT DEVIATE)
- Framework: Next.js 14+ App Router + TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + Custom CSS (globals.css variables)
- Animations: GSAP + ScrollTrigger + Framer Motion
- 3D/Canvas: Three.js + React Three Fiber + Drei
- Smooth Scroll: Lenis
- Icons: Lucide React
- State: Zustand
- Data: Modular TypeScript files in src/data/

## DESIGN DIRECTION (DO NOT DEVIATE)
- Aesthetic: Japanese Manga / Editorial / Cinematic Scroll-Telling
- Theme System: Day/Night Mode via Zustand (`themeStore`) and `.dark` class toggling.
- Primary Accent: Vermillion Red #E63946 (Japanese ink stamp)
- Secondary Accent: Aged Gold #F5E6C8 (parchment)
- Typography: Space Grotesk (English) + Noto Sans JP (Kanji)
- Signature: GSAP-drawn curvy SVG arrows connecting sections
- Cursor: Custom ink-drop canvas trail

## DO NOT TOUCH
- E:\git-workspace\git-workspace-2026-onwards\portfolio (OLD PROJECT — NEVER MODIFY)

## CODE STYLE & CONVENTIONS
- Use TypeScript strictly — no `any` types
- Use `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes
- Component files: PascalCase (.tsx)
- Data files: camelCase (.ts)
- Always add JSDoc comments to components explaining their purpose
- Use named exports, not default exports for components (except pages)
- 'use client' usage: Only at the top of interactive components (GSAP, Framer Motion, Three.js, event listeners). Keep layouts server-rendered where possible.
